  "copy": {
    "caption": "Building a fresh bedroom in the treetops every single night.",
    "shortDescription": "Orangutans are the only great apes that live mostly alone instead of in groups, and they spend almost their entire lives up in the forest canopy. Every evening they build a new sleeping platform from bent branches and leaves — a fresh, comfortable nest ten to thirty meters off the ground. They have the longest childhood of any non-human animal, staying with and learning from their mothers for up to eight years. Fun fact: Orangutans have been observed making raincoats out of large leaves during downpours, holding them above their heads."
